
Description
===========

A port of the janrain capture demo site from php into a ruby on rails app.

Installation and Setup
======================

* Clone.

* Move example_config.yml to config.yml and modify the values to your configuration.

* Start rails server.

Documentation
=============

DemoController
--------------

Controller for the following user viewable actions:

* demo/home
* demo/profile
* demo/edit_profile
  

and back-end actions

* demo/authCallback
  Handles authentication callback from capture
* demo/logout
  Signs out of site, mostly for callbacks from sso sites.
* demo/xdcomm
  For cross domain scripts.

DemoController also populates variables used by partials

* _navigation.html.erb
  Renders welcome message and links to site pages.
* _backplane.html.erb
  Includes and configures backplane.
* _sso.html.erb
  Includes and configures SSO.

Layouts and Views
-----------------

Each publicly accesible page(home, profile, edit_profile) has a view.

These views are rendered within a single layout, demo_layout, which also renders the navigation bar, sso and backplane partials.

Helpers
-------

* SessionHelper
  Tracks signin state using the session hash, and exposes the capture api, specifically settings/items and entity
* Settings
  Loads configuration from config.yml in rails root.

